==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Piazza
<hw>Pi*az"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Piazzas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[It., place, square, market
place, L. <ets>platea</ets> street, courtyard. See
<er>Place</er>.]</ety> <def>An open square in a European town,
especially an Italian town; hence <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, an arcaded and
roofed gallery; a portico. In the United States the word is popularly
applied to a veranda.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We walk by the obelisk, and meditate in <qex>piazzas</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pibcorn</ent>⟦br⟧
